	<div class="maincontainer">
		<div class="header"><h1>Patrick Verga</h1></div>
		<div class="main">
			<p>I'm a PhD candidate at 
				<a href="http://www.cs.umass.edu">UMass Amherst</a> 
				working in the 
				<a href="http://www.iesl.cs.umass.edu/">Information Extraction and Synthesis Laboratory (IESL)</a> 
				with Professor 
				<a href="http://people.cs.umass.edu/~mccallum/">Andrew McCallum</a>. 
				Previously at UMass, I recieved my M.S. in Computer Science in Fall 2014 as well as my B.S. in Neuroscience and B.A. in Computer Science in May 2012. I also worked as a Software Engineering Intern at 
				<a href="http://www.tripadvisor.com">TripAdvisor</a>. 
				
			</p>
<!--			
			<h1>Research Interests</h1>
			<p><strong>I am interested in how to represent and retrieve information. </strong></p> 
			<p>I'm broadly interested in memory and learning and have worked in cognitive psychology, neuroscience, and computer science. I'm currently working in information retrieval using entities and embedded representations to more effectively determine relevance. This could be within a large static set of documents like a snapshot of the internet, or across time such as in several hundred years worth of published books.
-->

